trend_summary: 2000-2020 imagery shows low-density development amid dominant forest. Industrial estates and quarrying enlarge in the northwest, a few residential pockets appear along the main highway, and the eastern airfield gains extra aprons and service buildings. Overall vegetation remains extensive, with localized clear-cuts replacing woodland.
notable_changes: Eastern airport: wider apron, new hangars and service roads.
North-west industrial zone expands southward with larger roofs and paved yards.
Main east-west highway straightened and dual-lane sections added.
Small residential clusters infill forest clearings near central road junctions.
